        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 4:32PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 432 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Statesville, or 4 miles east of Stony Point,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Statesville, Stony Point, Harmony, Love Valley, Cleveland, Hiddenite,
Turnersburg, Olin, Sheffield, and Scotts.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
